{
  "id": "c0c0c0c0-0010-0000-0000-000000000000",
  "name": "Silent Update Pattern",
  "type": "871ae771-b9b1-4f40-8c7f-d9038bfb69c3",
  "created": 1738454400000,
  "modified": 1773243817442,
  "content": {
    "description": [
      ":doc",
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "The Silent Update pattern solves a fundamental tension in Hobson: saving data to the database normally triggers a re-render, but during user interactions like dragging, re-rendering destroys the DOM and breaks the interaction mid-flight."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "The Problem"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "Hobson's reactive rendering means any call to "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "api.update(item)"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " triggers a full re-render of the affected item. This is usually desirable — when you edit a note, you want to see the change. But during continuous interactions:"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":ul",
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":strong",
              {
                "s": "Dragging a window"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " generates position updates on every mouse move"
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":strong",
              {
                "s": "Resizing"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " generates size updates continuously"
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":strong",
              {
                "s": "Z-index changes"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " when clicking to bring a window to front"
            }
          ]
        ]
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "If each of these triggered a re-render, the DOM would be destroyed and recreated mid-drag, losing:"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":ul",
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            {
              "s": "The drag interaction itself"
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            {
              "s": "Scroll positions within windows"
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            {
              "s": "Focus state (which element has focus)"
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            {
              "s": "Text selection ranges"
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            {
              "s": "Textarea cursor positions"
            }
          ]
        ]
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "The Solution: Two-Tier Save"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":code-block",
        {
          "s": "// Normal update — saves AND re-renders\nawait api.update(item);\n\n// Silent update — saves WITHOUT re-rendering\nawait api.set(item);"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "api.set()"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " writes to IndexedDB but does not trigger a re-render. "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "api.update()"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " writes AND re-renders. The calling code chooses which to use based on context."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "When to Use Each"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":table",
        [
          ":thead",
          [
            ":tr",
            [
              ":th",
              {
                "s": "Scenario"
              }
            ],
            [
              ":th",
              {
                "s": "Method"
              }
            ],
            [
              ":th",
              {
                "s": "Why"
              }
            ]
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":tbody",
          [
            ":tr",
            [
              ":td",
              {
                "s": "Position updates during drag"
              }
            ],
            [
              ":td",
              [
                ":code",
                {
                  "s": "api.set()"
                }
              ]
            ],
            [
              ":td",
              {
                "s": "DOM must survive"
              }
            ]
          ],
          [
            ":tr",
            [
              ":td",
              {
                "s": "Z-index change (click to front)"
              }
            ],
            [
              ":td",
              [
                ":code",
                {
                  "s": "api.set()"
                }
              ]
            ],
            [
              ":td",
              {
                "s": "Only need "
              },
              [
                ":code",
                {
                  "s": "style.zIndex"
                }
              ],
              {
                "s": " change"
              }
            ]
          ],
          [
            ":tr",
            [
              ":td",
              {
                "s": "Resize during handle drag"
              }
            ],
            [
              ":td",
              [
                ":code",
                {
                  "s": "api.set()"
                }
              ]
            ],
            [
              ":td",
              {
                "s": "DOM must survive"
              }
            ]
          ],
          [
            ":tr",
            [
              ":td",
              {
                "s": "Adding/removing an attachment"
              }
            ],
            [
              ":td",
              [
                ":code",
                {
                  "s": "api.update()"
                }
              ]
            ],
            [
              ":td",
              {
                "s": "New DOM element needed"
              }
            ]
          ],
          [
            ":tr",
            [
              ":td",
              {
                "s": "Changing item content"
              }
            ],
            [
              ":td",
              [
                ":code",
                {
                  "s": "api.update()"
                }
              ]
            ],
            [
              ":td",
              {
                "s": "Content must re-render"
              }
            ]
          ],
          [
            ":tr",
            [
              ":td",
              {
                "s": "Changing item type"
              }
            ],
            [
              ":td",
              [
                ":code",
                {
                  "s": "api.update()"
                }
              ]
            ],
            [
              ":td",
              {
                "s": "May need different view"
              }
            ]
          ],
          [
            ":tr",
            [
              ":td",
              {
                "s": "View config update (axis, layout)"
              }
            ],
            [
              ":td",
              [
                ":code",
                {
                  "s": "silent: true"
                }
              ]
            ],
            [
              ":td",
              {
                "s": "View config is metadata — must not trigger parent re-render"
              }
            ]
          ]
        ]
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "The Trade-off"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "Silent updates preserve DOM state but create the "
        },
        [
          ":item-ref",
          {
            "s": "c0c0c0c0-0011-0000-0000-000000000000"
          },
          {
            "s": "Stale Closure"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " problem. After a silent update, the database has current state but JavaScript closures from render time hold old state. Event handlers must read fresh data from the database."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "Implementation Notes"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "The pattern applies to the kernel's storage/rendering split:"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":ul",
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "kernel.storage.set()"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " — pure storage, no side effects"
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "kernel.rendering.renderItem()"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " — triggers render cycle"
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "api.update()"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " combines both; "
            },
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "api.set()"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " is storage-only"
            }
          ]
        ]
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "Views that use silent updates should also update the DOM directly for immediate visual feedback (e.g., setting "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "wrapper.style.left"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " during drag), then persist the final state on mouse-up."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "See Also"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":ul",
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
